The paper focuses on deep learning models, specifically dilated convolutional networks, and their ability to represent rich classes of functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a new concept, mixed tensor decompositions, which could potentially fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The use of convolutional networks also suggests that the paper could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
